hopobject.body: Where's the nearest cash machine? eggstractor Adequately supervising these firms will take tremendous resources and expertise the Fed currently does not have. The 2013 operating budget of the Fed was up 6.5 percent year-over-year, but this is hardly enough to compensate for the massive increase in the responsibilities. The Federal Reserve has roughly a $3.5 billion budget, whereas the 50 largest U.S. banks hold $15 trillion in assets. This is David versus Goliath.
